{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "KITTI:The Karlsruhe Institute of Technology and Toyota Technological Institute (KITTI) dataset [72] is provided by the Karlsruhe Institute of Technology (KIT), Germany, and is suitable for benchmarking stereo vision, optical flow, 3D tracking, 3D object detection or simultaneous localization and mapping (SLAM) algorithms.",
    "It is widely regarded as one of the most prestigious datasets in the field of autonomous driving.",
    "To date, it has been cited more than 2,000 times in the literature.",
    "The data collection vehicle is equipped with multiple high-resolution color and greyscale stereo cameras, a Velodyne 3D Lidar, and high-precision Global Positioning System (GPS) and Inertial Measurement Unit (GPS/IMU) sensors.",
    "It provides a total of six hours of driving data collected in rural and motorway traffic scenarios around Karlsruhe.The area around Karlsruhe."
  ],
